<div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> › <a href="almanac-home.dc.html">Almanac</a> › <span>Lunar Tarot</span></div>
<header><h1>Reading Tarot With the Lunar Cycle</h1><p class="article-meta">Published 13 July 2026</p><p class="lead">Use each moon phase to shape your intentions, daily cards, and full moon reflections. A practice that returns each month, deepening with every turn.</p></header>
<section class="alt-bg"><div class="max-width"><div class="content-block"><p class="content-text">The moon has a rhythm: dark, growing, full, and fading. Your tarot practice can follow that same rhythm. Each phase invites a different kind of reading, a different kind of question. Over eight phases, you move from planting intention to releasing what no longer serves.</p></div><h2>The Eight Moon Phases</h2><div class="moon-phase-grid"><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌑</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">New Moon</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Beginning</div><p class="moon-phase-text">The darkest night. A moment of pause before growth. Ask yourself: "What am I ready to begin?" Draw one card for the seed of intention you're planting this month.</p></div><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌒</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">Waxing Crescent</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Action</div><p class="moon-phase-text">The first curve of light appears. Energy is rising. Daily draw: "What action will serve this intention today?" Small steps, steady forward.</p></div><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌓</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">First Quarter</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Challenge</div><p class="moon-phase-text">Half light, half dark. A moment of testing. Ask: "What obstacle is teaching me?" The cards here often show what wants to be seen, not what's comfortable.</p></div><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌔</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">Waxing Gibbous</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Refinement</div><p class="moon-phase-text">The light grows fuller. You're getting closer. Daily draw: "What needs adjusting?" Fine-tune your approach. The answer is almost visible.</p></div><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌕</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">Full Moon</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Illumination</div><p class="moon-phase-text">Everything is lit. Nothing is hidden. This is your major reading: three to five cards, deep reflection. Ask: "What is being revealed to me?" "What have I learned?" "What pattern do I see?"</p></div><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌖</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">Waning Gibbous</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Integration</div><p class="moon-phase-text">The light begins to fade. Time to take what you've learned and let it settle. Daily draw: "What wisdom am I carrying forward?" Gratitude reading.</p></div><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌗</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">Last Quarter</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Release</div><p class="moon-phase-text">Half light again, but fading. Ask: "What am I ready to release?" "What no longer belongs with me?" The cards here show the door closing—and that's the point.</p></div><div class="moon-phase-card"><div class="moon-phase-header"><div class="moon-icon">🌘</div><div><h3 class="moon-phase-name">Waning Crescent</h3></div></div><div class="moon-phase-focus">Focus: Rest</div><p class="moon-phase-text">Nearly dark again. The cycle is completing. Pause. Reflect. Daily draw: "What will I carry into the next cycle?" Then rest. The new moon is coming.</p></div></div></div></section>
<section><div class="max-width"><h2>How to Begin</h2><div class="content-block"><p class="content-text">You don't need to start at the new moon. Start today, wherever the moon is. Draw one card for this phase's focus. Tomorrow, draw another. Over the next 29 days, you'll complete the circle and understand how your practice deepens with the rhythm of the sky.</p><p class="content-text" style="margin-top:20px;">Many people find that reading with the lunar cycle transforms their relationship with tarot. The repetition isn't boring—it's a deepening. The same questions, asked month after month, reveal layers you missed before.</p></div></div></section>
